	   <tr><td colspan=2>LVL 48 Druid with 194 wis .<br> Hello friends , I know we all love Broog Blackbeard when he comes tearing through the zone . But I was looking for a dark blue con to take down and didn't look at target till I had snared dear Broog . So lo and behold I have Broog Blackbeard on the string and by the way I do look at target before snaring now. Well I had him jogging behind me and had seen him desimate mid 50's palyers so what was I to do ? Since I could zone if I had to there was tht option . But if I went link dead I would be toast . So what the heck , I Doted Broog with Drifting Death which he resisted but I used Immolate another Dot which held. He resisted drifting 3 times off and on which was followed by Immolate then drifting death again which would hold . I kited him for 20 to 30 min and snared him twice in the interum .With the resists my mana was used up but I would run ahead and med as he cought up , and take off again . I would Dot with drifting when needed . But after a long time my mana was about used up . He was down to 20% life and I had to med till I got enough mana to hit him with Drifting again , then the inevitable happened , at least at my lvl . My mana ran out . But it was almost enough Broog was in his death run with 12% life left and then my snare spell wore off . Oh no , no mana and no time to med up because he was off and away .So since my 1hb is up to 157 which I'm glad I worked on it( and I was using a 1hb at the time) I proceded to beat the ever loving &quot;S&quot; out of him while he cried along the way . When the ensnare spell wore off I had him over by the Inn close to the Lake Rathe zone , so he starts heading for home back to hg valley and He thinks help from his brother HG's . I beat on him from there to the entrance to HG valley where he finally expired and the reward was.... really not much . 4 pp and about 1/2 a blue exp if that much . So the moral to this story is keep your weapons skill as high as you can , it can come in handy , and don't bother killing Broog . Its not worth it , I could have taken 3 to 4 regular HG's in the same time and been much farther ahead in the pp and exp dept. Oh also if I had gone LD I would have been burnt mashed toast to say the least . <br><br>Safe Travels To All...<br>Riada Wohali Druid of the 48th Season<br>Lifeblood of Surefall Guild member<br>Bristlebane Server<br>&nbsp;<br>Riada Wohali " A Seeker Of Knowledge "</td></tr>
